Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Template Designer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/template-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/template-designer-6-7)

With the help of Free Texts the FO code can be enriched with individual statements. Right click first on the desired element and select Edit Free Texts in the context menu.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 170. Free Texts*

The element with configured free texts is now marked with a matching "F" icon.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 171. block with "F" icon*

Via the "XSLT-FO" view you can now see where the entries are put in the FO-code:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 172. Free Texts - "XSLT-FO" view*

> Note

This function inserts the texts directly into the XSL-FO and tries to transform them on rendering. The PDF preview could not be generated, if the specified texts are incorrect.
